{
    "CAMPAIGN_TITLE_THE_BETHEL_REBELLION": "The Bethel Rebellion",
    "TBR_DESC_SHORT": "An Alliance fleet deep within enemy territory must create an opening for the rest of the invasion force, but the truth behind the rebellion makes their mission far more complicated than they had ever imagined.",
    "TBR_DESC_DIFFICULTY": "Difficulty Recommendations:\nEASY - New Players (Solo)\nMEDIUM - New Players (Co-op) and Experienced Players (Solo)\nHARD - Experienced Players (Co-op) and Very Experienced Players (Solo)",
    "TBR_DESC_LONG": "The Shelter Alliance has finally fractured.  The destruction of an agricultural station by Protectorate Separatists is the match cast upon the tinder of nearly five centuries of simmering resentment between the Alliance’s thirteen member nations.\n\nIn a desperate attempt to quell the rebellion before it can rip the rest of the Alliance apart, Fleet Admiral Winchester has been ordered to invade the Bethel system and given a blank check to do so.  However, with the entire invasion fleet forced to transit the narrow aperture of Bethel’s only hyperspace gate, casualties are expected to be catastrophically high.  The discovery of a fortuitous, but extremely treacherous, natural hyperspace route has presented an opportunity for a small diversion force to sneak into the system without having to use the gate.  Admiral Winchester has selected you to lead this force.\n\nTake command of the scattered remains of Task Force Alder as it arrives in the Bethel system in what will be the most important, and most dangerous, mission of your naval career.  You have only a few days left to draw the defenders off the gate before the invasion fleet comes through.  What awaits them at the exit depends on you.\n\nThe future of the Alliance, and whether or not it will collapse into total civil war, hinges on the success or failure of the Bethel Rebellion.",

